const eu = Pe("Zap", [["polygon", {
    points: "13 2 3 14 12 14 11 22 21 10 12 10 13 2",
    key: "45s27k"
}]]);
function AO(t, e) {
    if (typeof t == "function")
        return t(e);
    t != null && (t.current = e)
}
function rR(...t) {
    return e => {
        let r = !1;
        const n = t.map(i => {
            const a = AO(i, e);
            return !r && typeof a == "function" && (r = !0),
            a
        }
        );
        if (r)
            return () => {
                for (let i = 0; i < n.length; i++) {
                    const a = n[i];
                    typeof a == "function" ? a() : AO(t[i], null)
                }
            }
    }
}
function St(...t) {

            cancelable: !0
        });

        window.dispatchEvent(u),

    }

}

class Gq {
    constructor() {
        this.HEADER_LENGTH = 1
    }

        return e.constructor === ArrayBuffer ? r(this._binaryDecode(e)) : r(typeof e == "string" ? JSON.parse(e) : {})
    }
    _binaryDecode(e) {
        const r = new DataView(e)
          , n = new TextDecoder;
        return this._decodeBroadcast(e, r, n)
    }
    _decodeBroadcast(e, r, n) {

          , a = r.getUint8(2);

        o = o + i;

        }
    }

        }

class nv {
    constructor(e, r, n={}, i=mR) {
        this.channel = e,
        this.event = r,
        this.payload = n,
        this.timeout = i,
        this.sent = !1,
        this.timeoutTimer = void 0,
        this.ref = "",
        this.receivedResp = null,
        this.recHooks = [],
        this.refEvent = null
    }
    resend(e) {
        this.timeout = e,
        this._cancelRefEvent(),
        this.ref = "",
        this.refEvent = null,
        this.receivedResp = null,
        this.sent = !1,
        this.send()
    }
    send() {
        this._hasReceived("timeout") || (this.startTimeout(),
        this.sent = !0,
        this.channel.socket.push({
            topic: this.channel.topic,
            event: this.event,
            payload: this.payload,
            ref: this.ref,
            join_ref: this.channel._joinRef()
        }))
    }
    updatePayload(e) {
        this.payload = Object.assign(Object.assign({}, this.payload), e)
    }
    receive(e, r) {
        var n;
        return this._hasReceived(e) && r((n = this.receivedResp) === null || n === void 0 ? void 0 : n.response),
        this.recHooks.push({
            status: e,
            callback: r
        }),
        this
    }
    startTimeout() {
        if (this.timeoutTimer)
            return;
        this.ref = this.channel.socket._makeRef(),
        this.refEvent = this.channel._replyEventName(this.ref);
        const e = r => {
            this._cancelRefEvent(),
            this._cancelTimeout(),
            this.receivedResp = r,
            this._matchReceive(r)
        }
        ;
        this.channel._on(this.refEvent, {}, e),
        this.timeoutTimer = setTimeout( () => {
            this.trigger("timeout", {})
        }
        , this.timeout)
    }
    trigger(e, r) {
        this.refEvent && this.channel._trigger(this.refEvent, {
            status: e,
            response: r
        })
    }
    destroy() {
        this._cancelRefEvent(),
        this._cancelTimeout()
    }
    _cancelRefEvent() {
        this.refEvent && this.channel._off(this.refEvent, {})
    }
    _cancelTimeout() {
        clearTimeout(this.timeoutTimer),
        this.timeoutTimer = void 0
    }
    _matchReceive({status: e, response: r}) {
        this.recHooks.filter(n => n.status === e).forEach(n => n.callback(r))
    }
    _hasReceived(e) {
        return this.receivedResp && this.receivedResp.status === e
    }
}

class qc {
    constructor(e, r) {
        this.channel = e,
        this.state = {},
        this.pendingDiffs = [],
        this.joinRef = null,
        this.caller = {
            onJoin: () => {}
            ,
            onLeave: () => {}
            ,
            onSync: () => {}
        };
        const n = r?.events || {
            state: "presence_state",
            diff: "presence_diff"
        };
        this.channel._on(n.state, {}, i => {
            const {onJoin: a, onLeave: o, onSync: c} = this.caller;
            this.joinRef = this.channel._joinRef(),
            this.state = qc.syncState(this.state, i, a, o),
            this.pendingDiffs.forEach(u => {
                this.state = qc.syncDiff(this.state, u, a, o)
            }
            ),
            this.pendingDiffs = [],
            c()
        }
        ),
        this.channel._on(n.diff, {}, i => {
            const {onJoin: a, onLeave: o, onSync: c} = this.caller;
            this.inPendingSyncState() ? this.pendingDiffs.push(i) : (this.state = qc.syncDiff(this.state, i, a, o),
            c())
        }
        ),
        this.onJoin( (i, a, o) => {
            this.channel._trigger("presence", {
                event: "join",
                key: i,
                currentPresences: a,
                newPresences: o
            })
        }
        ),
        this.onLeave( (i, a, o) => {
            this.channel._trigger("presence", {
                event: "leave",
                key: i,
                currentPresences: a,
                leftPresences: o
            })
        }
        ),
        this.onSync( () => {
            this.channel._trigger("presence", {
                event: "sync"
            })
        }
        )
    }
    static syncState(e, r, n, i) {
        const a = this.cloneDeep(e)
          , o = this.transformState(r)
          , c = {}
          , u = {};
        return this.map(a, (d, p) => {
            o[d] || (u[d] = p)
        }
        ),
        this.map(o, (d, p) => {
            const m = a[d];
            if (m) {
                const g = p.map(y => y.presence_ref)
                  , b = m.map(y => y.presence_ref)
                  , w = p.filter(y => b.indexOf(y.presence_ref) < 0)
                  , x = m.filter(y => g.indexOf(y.presence_ref) < 0);
                w.length > 0 && (c[d] = w),
                x.length > 0 && (u[d] = x)
            } else
                c[d] = p
        }
        ),
        this.syncDiff(a, {
            joins: c,
            leaves: u
        }, n, i)
    }
    static syncDiff(e, r, n, i) {
        const {joins: a, leaves: o} = {
            joins: this.transformState(r.joins),
            leaves: this.transformState(r.leaves)
        };
        return n || (n = () => {}
        ),
        i || (i = () => {}
        ),
        this.map(a, (c, u) => {
            var d;
            const p = (d = e[c]) !== null && d !== void 0 ? d : [];
            if (e[c] = this.cloneDeep(u),
            p.length > 0) {
                const m = e[c].map(b => b.presence_ref)
                  , g = p.filter(b => m.indexOf(b.presence_ref) < 0);
                e[c].unshift(...g)
            }
            n(c, p, u)
        }
        ),
        this.map(o, (c, u) => {
            let d = e[c];
            if (!d)
                return;
            const p = u.map(m => m.presence_ref);
            d = d.filter(m => p.indexOf(m.presence_ref) < 0),
            e[c] = d,
            i(c, d, u),
            d.length === 0 && delete e[c]
        }
        ),
        e
    }
    static map(e, r) {
        return Object.getOwnPropertyNames(e).map(n => r(n, e[n]))
    }
    static transformState(e) {
        return e = this.cloneDeep(e),
        Object.getOwnPropertyNames(e).reduce( (r, n) => {
            const i = e[n];
            return "metas"in i ? r[n] = i.metas.map(a => (a.presence_ref = a.phx_ref,
            delete a.phx_ref,
            delete a.phx_ref_prev,
            a)) : r[n] = i,
            r
        }
        , {})
    }
    static cloneDeep(e) {
        return JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(e))
    }
    onJoin(e) {
        this.caller.onJoin = e
    }
    onLeave(e) {
        this.caller.onLeave = e
    }
    onSync(e) {
        this.caller.onSync = e
    }
    inPendingSyncState() {
        return !this.joinRef || this.joinRef !== this.channel._joinRef()
    }
}

class D1 {

    subscribe(e, r=this.timeout) {
        var n, i;
        if (this.socket.isConnected() || this.socket.connect(),
        this.state == mr.closed) {

            this._onError(p => e?.(Si.CHANNEL_ERROR, p)),

                presence: o,

                config: d

                var m;

                p === void 0) {
                    e?.(Si.SUBSCRIBED);
                    return
                } else {
                    const g = this.bindings.postgres_changes
                      , b = (m = g?.length) !== null && m !== void 0 ? m : 0
                      , w = [];
                    for (let x = 0; x < b; x++) {
                        const y = g[x]
                          , {filter: {event: P, schema: S, table: j, filter: k}} = y
                          , E = p && p[x];

                            w.push(Object.assign(Object.assign({}, y), {
                                id: E.id
                            }));
                        else {
                            this.unsubscribe(),
                            this.state = mr.errored,
                            e?.(Si.CHANNEL_ERROR, new Error("mismatch between server and client bindings for postgres changes"));
                            return
                        }
                    }

                    e && e(Si.SUBSCRIBED);

                }
            }
            ).receive("error", p => {
                this.state = mr.errored,
                e?.(Si.CHANNEL_ERROR, new Error(JSON.stringify(Object.values(p).join(", ") || "error")))
            }
            ).receive("timeout", () => {
                e?.(Si.TIMED_OUT)
            }
            )
        }

    }
    presenceState() {
        return this.presence.state
    }
    async track(e, r={}) {

            type: "presence",

        }, r.timeout || this.timeout)
    }
    async untrack(e={}) {

            type: "presence",
            event: "untrack"
        }, e)
    }
    on(e, r, n) {
        return this._on(e, r, n)

    async send(e, r={}) {
        var n, i;
        if (!this._canPush() && e.type === "broadcast") {
            const {event: a, payload: o} = e
              , u = {
                method: "POST",
                headers: {
                    Authorization: this.socket.accessTokenValue ? `Bearer ${this.socket.accessTokenValue}` : "",

                    "Content-Type": "application/json"
                },

                    messages: [{
                        topic: this.subTopic,

                        payload: o,
                        private: this.private
                    }]
                })
            };

                d.ok ? "ok" : "error"
            } catch (d) {
                return d.name === "AbortError" ? "timed out" : "error"
            }
        } else
            return new Promise(a => {
                var o, c, u;
                const d = this._push(e.type, e, r.timeout || this.timeout);
                e.type === "broadcast" && !(!((u = (c = (o = this.params) === null || o === void 0 ? void 0 : o.config) === null || c === void 0 ? void 0 : c.broadcast) === null || u === void 0) && u.ack) && a("ok"),
                d.receive("ok", () => a("ok")),
                d.receive("error", () => a("error")),
                d.receive("timeout", () => a("timed out"))
            }
            )
    }

    }
    unsubscribe(e=this.timeout) {

        const r = () => {
            this.socket.log("channel", `leave ${this.topic}`),
            this._trigger(On.close, "leave", this._joinRef())
        }
        ;
        this.joinPush.destroy();

            n = new nv(this,On.leave,{},e),
            n.receive("ok", () => {
                r(),
                i("ok")
            }
            ).receive("timeout", () => {
                r(),
                i("timed out")
            }
            ).receive("error", () => {
                i("error")
            }
            ),

        }
        ).finally( () => {

        }
        )
    }
    teardown() {

        this.rejoinTimer && clearTimeout(this.rejoinTimer.timer),
        this.joinPush.destroy()
    }
    async _fetchWithTimeout(e, r, n) {
        const i = new AbortController
          , a = setTimeout( () => i.abort(), n)
          , o = await this.socket.fetch(e, Object.assign(Object.assign({}, r), {
            signal: i.signal
        }));

        o
    }
    _push(e, r, n=this.timeout) {

function F6(t, e, r) {

    async _reauthenticate() {
        try {
            return await this._useSession(async e => {
                const {data: {session: r}, error: n} = e;
                if (n)
                    throw n;
                if (!r)
                    throw new ga;

                    jwt: r.access_token
                });
                return {
                    data: {
                        user: null,
                        session: null
                    },
                    error: i
                }
            }
            )
        } catch (e) {
            if (Be(e))
                return {
                    data: {
                        user: null,
                        session: null
                    },
                    error: e
                };
            throw e
        }
    }
    async resend(e) {
        try {

    async getSession() {
        return await this.initializePromise,
        await this._acquireLock(-1, async () => this._useSession(async r => r))
    }
    async _acquireLock(e, r) {
        this._debug("#_acquireLock", "begin", e);
        try {
            if (this.lockAcquired) {
                const n = this.pendingInLock.length ? this.pendingInLock[this.pendingInLock.length - 1] : Promise.resolve()
                  , i = (async () => (await n,
                await r()))();
                return this.pendingInLock.push((async () => {
                    try {
                        await i
                    } catch {}
                }
                )()),
                i
            }
            return await this.lock(`lock:${this.storageKey}`, e, async () => {
                this._debug("#_acquireLock", "lock acquired for storage key", this.storageKey);
                try {
                    this.lockAcquired = !0;
                    const n = r();
                    for (this.pendingInLock.push((async () => {
                        try {
                            await n
                        } catch {}
                    }
                    )()),
                    await n; this.pendingInLock.length; ) {
                        const i = [...this.pendingInLock];
                        await Promise.all(i),
                        this.pendingInLock.splice(0, i.length)
                    }
                    return await n
                } finally {
                    this._debug("#_acquireLock", "lock released for storage key", this.storageKey),
                    this.lockAcquired = !1
                }
            }
            )
        } finally {
            this._debug("#_acquireLock", "end")
        }
    }
    async _useSession(e) {
        this._debug("#_useSession", "begin");
        try {
            const r = await this.__loadSession();
            return await e(r)
        } finally {
            this._debug("#_useSession", "end")
        }
    }
    async __loadSession() {
        this._debug("#__loadSession()", "begin"),
        this.lockAcquired || this._debug("#__loadSession()", "used outside of an acquired lock!", new Error().stack);
        try {
            let e = null;
            const r = await oo(this.storage, this.storageKey);
            if (this._debug("#getSession()", "session from storage", r),
            r !== null && (this._isValidSession(r) ? e = r : (this._debug("#getSession()", "session from storage is not valid"),
            await this._removeSession())),
            !e)
                return {
                    data: {
                        session: null
                    },
                    error: null
                };
            const n = e.expires_at ? e.expires_at * 1e3 - Date.now() < av : !1;
            if (this._debug("#__loadSession()", `session has${n ? "" : " not"} expired`, "expires_at", e.expires_at),
            !n) {
                if (this.userStorage) {
                    const o = await oo(this.userStorage, this.storageKey + "-user");
                    o?.user ? e.user = o.user : e.user = lv()
                }
                if (this.storage.isServer && e.user) {
                    let o = this.suppressGetSessionWarning;
                    e = new Proxy(e,{
                        get: (u, d, p) => (!o && d === "user" && (console.warn("Using the user object as returned from supabase.auth.getSession() or from some supabase.auth.onAuthStateChange() events could be insecure! This value comes directly from the storage medium (usually cookies on the server) and may not be authentic. Use supabase.auth.getUser() instead which authenticates the data by contacting the Supabase Auth server."),
                        o = !0,
                        this.suppressGetSessionWarning = !0),
                        Reflect.get(u, d, p))
                    })
                }
                return {
                    data: {
                        session: e
                    },
                    error: null
                }
            }
            const {session: i, error: a} = await this._callRefreshToken(e.refresh_token);
            return a ? {
                data: {
                    session: null
                },
                error: a
            } : {
                data: {
                    session: i
                },
                error: null
            }
        } finally {
            this._debug("#__loadSession()", "end")
        }
    }
    async getUser(e) {

        await this._acquireLock(-1, async () => await this._getUser()))

                })

    }

    async _updateUser(e, r={}) {
        try {

                if (a)
                    throw a;
                if (!i.session)

                  , u = null;

    async setSession(e) {
        return await this.initializePromise,
        await this._acquireLock(-1, async () => await this._setSession(e))
    }
    async _setSession(e) {
        try {
            if (!e.access_token || !e.refresh_token)
                throw new ga;
            const r = Date.now() / 1e3;
            let n = r
              , i = !0
              , a = null;
            const {payload: o} = sv(e.access_token);
            if (o.exp && (n = o.exp,
            i = n <= r),
            i) {
                const {session: c, error: u} = await this._callRefreshToken(e.refresh_token);
                if (u)
                    return {
                        data: {
                            user: null,
                            session: null
                        },
                        error: u
                    };
                if (!c)
                    return {
                        data: {
                            user: null,
                            session: null
                        },
                        error: null
                    };
                a = c
            } else {
                const {data: c, error: u} = await this._getUser(e.access_token);
                if (u)
                    throw u;
                a = {
                    access_token: e.access_token,
                    refresh_token: e.refresh_token,
                    user: c.user,
                    token_type: "bearer",
                    expires_in: n - r,
                    expires_at: n
                },
                await this._saveSession(a),
                await this._notifyAllSubscribers("SIGNED_IN", a)
            }
            return {
                data: {
                    user: a.user,
                    session: a
                },
                error: null
            }
        } catch (r) {
            if (Be(r))
                return {
                    data: {
                        session: null,
                        user: null
                    },
                    error: r
                };
            throw r
        }
    }
    async refreshSession(e) {
        return await this.initializePromise,
        await this._acquireLock(-1, async () => await this._refreshSession(e))
    }
    async _refreshSession(e) {
        try {
            return await this._useSession(async r => {
                var n;
                if (!e) {
                    const {data: o, error: c} = r;
                    if (c)
                        throw c;
                    e = (n = o.session) !== null && n !== void 0 ? n : void 0
                }
                if (!e?.refresh_token)
                    throw new ga;
                const {session: i, error: a} = await this._callRefreshToken(e.refresh_token);
                return a ? {
                    data: {
                        user: null,
                        session: null
                    },
                    error: a
                } : i ? {
                    data: {
                        user: i.user,
                        session: i
                    },
                    error: null
                } : {
                    data: {
                        user: null,
                        session: null
                    },
                    error: null
                }
            }
            )
        } catch (r) {
            if (Be(r))
                return {
                    data: {
                        user: null,
                        session: null
                    },
                    error: r
                };
            throw r
        }
    }
    async _getSessionFromURL(e, r) {
        try {
            if (!jn())
                throw new xf("No browser detected.");
            if (e.error || e.error_description || e.error_code)
                throw new xf(e.error_description || "Error in URL with unspecified error_description",{
                    error: e.error || "unspecified_error",
                    code: e.error_code || "unspecified_code"
                });
            switch (r) {
            case "implicit":
                if (this.flowType === "pkce")
                    throw new XO("Not a valid PKCE flow url.");
                break;
            case "pkce":
                if (this.flowType === "implicit")
                    throw new xf("Not a valid implicit grant flow url.");
                break;
            default:
            }
            if (r === "pkce") {
                if (this._debug("#_initialize()", "begin", "is PKCE flow", !0),
                !e.code)
                    throw new XO("No code detected.");
                const {data: S, error: j} = await this._exchangeCodeForSession(e.code);
                if (j)
                    throw j;
                const k = new URL(window.location.href);
                return k.searchParams.delete("code"),
                window.history.replaceState(window.history.state, "", k.toString()),
                {
                    data: {
                        session: S.session,
                        redirectType: null
                    },
                    error: null
                }
            }
            const {provider_token: n, provider_refresh_token: i, access_token: a, refresh_token: o, expires_in: c, expires_at: u, token_type: d} = e;
            if (!a || !c || !o || !d)
                throw new xf("No session defined in URL");
            const p = Math.round(Date.now() / 1e3)
              , m = parseInt(c);
            let g = p + m;
            u && (g = parseInt(u));
            const b = g - p;
            b * 1e3 <= Rs && console.warn(`@supabase/gotrue-js: Session as retrieved from URL expires in ${b}s, should have been closer to ${m}s`);
            const w = g - m;
            p - w >= 120 ? console.warn("@supabase/gotrue-js: Session as retrieved from URL was issued over 120s ago, URL could be stale", w, g, p) : p - w < 0 && console.warn("@supabase/gotrue-js: Session as retrieved from URL was issued in the future? Check the device clock for skew", w, g, p);
            const {data: x, error: y} = await this._getUser(a);
            if (y)
                throw y;
            const P = {
                provider_token: n,
                provider_refresh_token: i,
                access_token: a,
                expires_in: m,
                expires_at: g,
                refresh_token: o,
                token_type: d,
                user: x.user
            };
            return window.location.hash = "",
            this._debug("#_getSessionFromURL()", "clearing window.location.hash"),
            {
                data: {
                    session: P,
                    redirectType: e.type
                },
                error: null
            }
        } catch (n) {
            if (Be(n))
                return {
                    data: {
                        session: null,
                        redirectType: null
                    },
                    error: n
                };
            throw n
        }
    }
    _isImplicitGrantCallback(e) {
        return !!(e.access_token || e.error_description)
    }

    }

        scope: "global"
    }) {
        return await this._useSession(async r => {
            var n;
            const {data: i, error: a} = r;
            if (a)
                return {

                };

                const {error: c} = await this.admin.signOut(o, e);
                if (c && !(R6(c) && (c.status === 404 || c.status === 401 || c.status === 403)))
                    return {
                        error: c
                    }
            }
            return e !== "others" && (await this._removeSession(),

    }
    onAuthStateChange(e) {

    async _refreshAccessToken(e) {
        const r = `#_refreshAccessToken(${e.substring(0, 5)}...)`;
        this._debug(r, "begin");
        try {
            const n = Date.now();
            return await Y6(async i => (i > 0 && await K6(200 * Math.pow(2, i - 1)),
            this._debug(r, "refreshing attempt", i),
            await et(this.fetch, "POST", `${this.url}/token?grant_type=refresh_token`, {

                },

            })), (i, a) => {
                const o = 200 * Math.pow(2, i);
                return a && ov(a) && Date.now() + o - n < Rs
            }
            )
        } catch (n) {
            if (this._debug(r, "error", n),
            Be(n))
                return {
                    data: {
                        session: null,
                        user: null
                    },
                    error: n
                };
            throw n
        } finally {
            this._debug(r, "end")
        }
    }
    _isValidSession(e) {
        return typeof e == "object" && e !== null && "access_token"in e && "refresh_token"in e && "expires_at"in e
    }

    async _recoverAndRefresh() {
        var e, r;
        const n = "#_recoverAndRefresh()";
        this._debug(n, "begin");
        try {
            const i = await oo(this.storage, this.storageKey);
            if (i && this.userStorage) {
                let o = await oo(this.userStorage, this.storageKey + "-user");
                !this.storage.isServer && Object.is(this.storage, this.userStorage) && !o && (o = {
                    user: i.user
                },
                await Ms(this.userStorage, this.storageKey + "-user", o)),
                i.user = (e = o?.user) !== null && e !== void 0 ? e : lv()
            } else if (i && !i.user && !i.user) {
                const o = await oo(this.storage, this.storageKey + "-user");
                o && o?.user ? (i.user = o.user,
                await pa(this.storage, this.storageKey + "-user"),
                await Ms(this.storage, this.storageKey, i)) : i.user = lv()
            }
            if (this._debug(n, "session from storage", i),
            !this._isValidSession(i)) {
                this._debug(n, "session is not valid"),
                i !== null && await this._removeSession();
                return
            }
            const a = ((r = i.expires_at) !== null && r !== void 0 ? r : 1 / 0) * 1e3 - Date.now() < av;
            if (this._debug(n, `session has${a ? "" : " not"} expired with margin of ${av}s`),
            a) {
                if (this.autoRefreshToken && i.refresh_token) {
                    const {error: o} = await this._callRefreshToken(i.refresh_token);
                    o && (console.error(o),
                    ov(o) || (this._debug(n, "refresh failed with a non-retryable error, removing the session", o),
                    await this._removeSession()))
                }
            } else if (i.user && i.user.__isUserNotAvailableProxy === !0)
                try {
                    const {data: o, error: c} = await this._getUser(i.access_token);
                    !c && o?.user ? (i.user = o.user,
                    await this._saveSession(i),
                    await this._notifyAllSubscribers("SIGNED_IN", i)) : this._debug(n, "could not get user data, skipping SIGNED_IN notification")
                } catch (o) {
                    console.error("Error getting user data:", o),
                    this._debug(n, "error getting user data, skipping SIGNED_IN notification", o)
                }
            else
                await this._notifyAllSubscribers("SIGNED_IN", i)
        } catch (i) {
            this._debug(n, "error", i),
            console.error(i);
            return
        } finally {
            this._debug(n, "end")
        }
    }
    async _callRefreshToken(e) {
        var r, n;
        if (!e)
            throw new ga;
        if (this.refreshingDeferred)
            return this.refreshingDeferred.promise;
        const i = `#_callRefreshToken(${e.substring(0, 5)}...)`;
        this._debug(i, "begin");
        try {

                const r = e.message?.toLowerCase() || "";
                if (r.includes("user from sub claim in jwt does not exist") || r.includes("invalid jwt") || r.includes("no session"))
                    return console.log("No active user session - this is normal for new users"),
                    {
                        user: null,
                        error: {
                            message: "No session"
                        }
                    };
                console.error("Error getting current user:", e)
            }
            return {
                user: t,
                error: e
            }
        } catch (t) {
            return console.error("Error getting current user:", t),
            {
                user: null,
                error: t
            }
        }
    }
    ,
    onAuthStateChange: t => {
        try {
            return Gr.auth.onAuthStateChange(t)
        } catch (e) {
            return console.error("Error setting up auth state listener:", e),
            {
                data: {
                    subscription: null
                }
            }
        }
    }
}
  , Nt = {
    getProfile: async t => {
        try {
            const {token: e, error: r} = await uv();
            if (r)
                return console.error("Error getting access token:", r),
                {
                    data: null,
                    error: r
                };
            if (!e)
                return console.error("No access token available"),
                {
                    data: null,
                    error: {
                        message: "No active session found",
                        status: 401
                    }
                };
            const n = await fetch(`${Wb}/rest/v1/user_profiles?select=*&user_id=eq.${t}`, {
                method: "GET",
                headers: {
                    Authorization: `Bearer ${e}`,
                    apikey: Hb,
                    "Content-Type": "application/json",
                    Prefer: "return=representation"
                }
            });
            if (n.status === 401)
                return console.error("Unauthorized access to user profile"),
                {
                    data: null,
                    error: {
                        message: "Unauthorized access",
                        status: 401
                    }
                };
            if (!n.ok)
                return console.error("Error fetching user profile:", n.status, n.statusText),
                {
                    data: null,
                    error: {
                        message: `HTTP ${n.status}: ${n.statusText}`,
                        status: n.status
                    }
                };

            {
                data: null,
                error: null
            }) : {
                data: i[0],
                error: null
            }
        } catch (e) {
            return console.error("Error in getProfile:", e),
            {
                data: null,
                error: e
            }
        }
    }
    ,

                    data: null,
                    error: o
                };

                        status: 401

                method: "POST",
                headers: {
                    Authorization: `Bearer ${a}`,
                    apikey: Hb,
                    "Content-Type": "application/json",
                    Prefer: "return=representation"
                },
                body: JSON.stringify(c)
            });
            return u.status === 401 ? (console.error("Unauthorized access to create user profile"),
            {
                data: null,
                error: {
                    message: "Unauthorized access",
                    status: 401
                }
            }) : u.ok ? {

                error: null
            } : (console.error("Error creating user profile:", u.status, u.statusText),
            {
                data: null,
                error: {

                }
            })

                data: null,
                error: a
            }
        }

                {
                    data: null,

                {
                    data: null,
                    error: a
                };

                console.log("Profile does not exist, creating new profile for user:", t);

                        error: d

                {

                    error: null
                }

            const {data: o, error: c} = await Gr.from("user_profiles").update(e).eq("user_id", t).select().single();

            {
                data: null,
                error: c

                error: null
            }
        } catch (r) {
            return console.error("Error in updateProfile:", r),
            {
                data: null,
                error: r
            }
        }

  , xi = t => {
    if (!t)

Please try again." : e.includes("email not confirmed") ? "Please check your email and confirm your account before signing in." : e.includes("user already registered") ? "Please enter a valid email address." : e.includes("too many requests") ? "Too many attempts. Please wait a moment before trying again." : e.includes("network error") || e.includes("fetch") ? "Connection error. Please check your internet connection and try again." : e.includes("unauthorized") || e.includes("401") ? "Session expired. Please sign in again." : e.includes("not found") || e.includes("404") ? "Service temporarily unavailable. Please try again later." : e.includes("internal server error") || e.includes("500") ? "Server error. Please try again later." : "Something went wrong. Please try again."
}

function HW() {
    const [t,e] = O.useState({
        count: 0,
        limit: 10,
        plan: "free",
        monthlyCount: 0,
        monthlyLimit: 50
    })
      , [r,n] = O.useState(null)

      , o = O.useRef(null)
      , c = O.useRef(0)
      , u = O.useRef(0)
      , d = O.useCallback(async (g, b) => {
        try {
            const {data: {session: w}, error: x} = await Gr.auth.getSession();
            if (x || !w) {
                console.log("No active session found, skipping backend persistence");
                return
            }
            if (r) {
                const y = new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 7)
                  , {data: P, error: S} = await Nt.getProfile(r.id);
                if (!P && !S) {
                    const {error: k} = await Nt.createProfile(r.id, r.email, r.user_metadata?.username, r.user_metadata?.full_name);
                    if (k) {
                        console.error("Failed to create user profile for usage tracking:", k);
                        return
                    }
                }
                const {error: j} = await Nt.updateProfile(r.id, {
                    api_calls_today: g,
                    last_api_call_date: b,
                    api_calls_monthly: t.monthlyCount + 1,
                    last_api_call_month: y
                });
                j ? console.error("Failed to persist API usage:", j) : u.current = g
            }
        } catch (w) {
            console.error("Failed to persist API usage:", w)
        }
    }
    , [r, t.monthlyCount])
      , p = O.useCallback(async () => {
        try {
            const {data: {session: g}, error: b} = await Gr.auth.getSession();
            if (b) {
                console.error("Error getting session:", b);
                const U = new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0]
                  , M = JSON.parse(sessionStorage.getItem("anonUsage") || "{}");
                let $ = M.count || 0;
                M.date !== U && ($ = 0),
                e({
                    count: $,
                    limit: 10,
                    plan: "free"
                }),
                sessionStorage.setItem("anonUsage", JSON.stringify({
                    count: $,
                    date: U
                }));
                return
            }
            if (!g) {
                console.log("No active session found, using anonymous usage");
                const U = new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0]
                  , M = JSON.parse(sessionStorage.getItem("anonUsage") || "{}");
                let $ = M.count || 0;
                M.date !== U && ($ = 0),
                e({
                    count: $,
                    limit: 10,
                    plan: "free"
                }),
                sessionStorage.setItem("anonUsage", JSON.stringify({
                    count: $,
                    date: U
                }));
                return
            }
            const {user: w, error: x} = await Yn.getCurrentUser();
            if (x) {
                console.error("Error getting current user:", x);
                const U = new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0]
                  , M = JSON.parse(sessionStorage.getItem("anonUsage") || "{}");
                let $ = M.count || 0;
                M.date !== U && ($ = 0),
                e({
                    count: $,
                    limit: 10,
                    plan: "free"
                }),
                sessionStorage.setItem("anonUsage", JSON.stringify({
                    count: $,
                    date: U
                }));

            }
            n(w);
            const {data: y, error: P} = await Nt.getProfile(w.id);
            let S = y;
            if (!y && !P) {
                console.log("Creating user profile for:", w.id);
                const {data: U, error: M} = await Nt.createProfile(w.id, w.email, w.user_metadata?.username, w.user_metadata?.full_name);
                M ? (console.error("Error creating user profile:", M),
                S = null) : S = U
            } else
                P && (console.error("Error getting user profile:", P),
                S = null);
            const j = new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0]
              , k = new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 7)
              , E = S?.plan_type || "free"
              , C = zW[E]
              , N = WW[E];
            let I = S?.api_calls_today || 0
              , R = S?.api_calls_monthly || 0;
            if (S?.last_api_call_date !== j) {
                I = 0;
                const {error: U} = await Nt.updateProfile(w.id, {
                    api_calls_today: 0,
                    last_api_call_date: j
                });
                U && console.error("Failed to reset daily usage count:", U)
            }
            if (S?.last_api_call_month !== k) {
                R = 0;
                const {error: U} = await Nt.updateProfile(w.id, {
                    api_calls_monthly: 0,
                    last_api_call_month: k
                });
                U && console.error("Failed to reset monthly usage count:", U)
            }
            e({
                count: I,
                limit: C,
                plan: E,
                monthlyCount: R,
                monthlyLimit: N
            }),
            u.current = I,
            c.current = I
        } catch (g) {
            console.error("Error loading usage:", g);
            const b = new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0]
              , w = JSON.parse(sessionStorage.getItem("anonUsage") || "{}");
            let x = w.count || 0;
            w.date !== b && (x = 0),
            e({
                count: x,
                limit: 10,
                plan: "free"
            }),
            sessionStorage.setItem("anonUsage", JSON.stringify({
                count: x,
                date: b
            }))
        }
    }
    , []);
    O.useEffect( () => (p(),
    () => {
        o.current && clearTimeout(o.current)
    }
    ), [p]);
    const m = O.useCallback(async () => {
        const g = new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0];
        if (t.count >= t.limit || t.monthlyCount >= t.monthlyLimit)
            return a(!0),
            !1;
        const b = t.count + 1
          , w = t.monthlyCount + 1;
        if (e(x => ({
            ...x,
            count: b,
            monthlyCount: w
        })),
        r)
            c.current = b,
            o.current && clearTimeout(o.current),
            o.current = setTimeout( () => {
                c.current > u.current && d(c.current, g)
            }
            , 1e3);
        else
            try {
                sessionStorage.setItem("anonUsage", JSON.stringify({
                    count: b,
                    date: g
                }))
            } catch (x) {
                console.error("Failed to store anonymous API usage:", x)
            }
        return b >= t.limit * .8 && b < t.limit && alert(`Warning: You've used ${b} of ${t.limit} daily API calls. Consider upgrading your plan.`),
        w >= t.monthlyLimit * .8 && w < t.monthlyLimit && alert(`Warning: You've used ${w} of ${t.monthlyLimit} monthly API calls. Consider upgrading your plan.`),
        !0
    }
    , [t, r, d]);
    return {
        usage: t,
        trackApiCall: m,
        showUpgradeModal: i,
        setShowUpgradeModal: a,
        loadUsage: p
    }
}
function e$({usage: t, showLabel: e=!0, onFeedbackClick: r, user: n}) {

      , a = t.monthlyLimit === 1 / 0 ? 0 : t.monthlyCount / t.monthlyLimit * 100
      , o = i >= 80
      , c = a >= 80;
    return t.count >= t.limit,
    ii(),
    f.jsxs("div", {

                className: "flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center justify-between gap-2 text-sm",
                children: [f.jsxs("span", {
                    className: "text-gray-300 break-words",
                    children: ["Daily API Calls: ", t.count, " / ", t.limit === 1 / 0 ? "" : t.limit]
                }), f.jsx("div", {

                        children: t.plan.toUpperCase()
                    })
                })]
            })
        }), t.limit !== 1 / 0 && f.jsxs("div", {
            className: "space-y-1",
            children: [f.jsx("div", {
                className: "text-xs text-gray-400",
                children: "Daily Usage"
            }), f.jsx(J1, {
                value: i,

            })]
        }), o && t.limit !== 1 / 0 && f.jsxs(Jn, {
            className: "bg-yellow-900/20 border-yellow-500/30",
            children: [f.jsx(Ca, {
                className: "h-4 w-4 text-yellow-500 flex-shrink-0"

const Xs = () => {
    const t = "https://askapi-dev.onrender.com";
    return t.trim() ? t.trim() : "http://localhost:5000"
}
  , ks = async t => {
    try {
        const e = await fetch(`${Xs()}/get-api-key`, {
            method: "POST",
            headers: {
                "Content-Type": "application/json"
            },
            body: JSON.stringify({
                service: t
            })
        });
        if (!e.ok)
            throw new Error(`HTTP error! status: ${e.status}`);
        return (await e.json()).api_key
    } catch {
        return null
    }
}
  , YW = async t => {
    try {
        console.log(" OCR Debug: Starting image OCR processing"),
        console.log(" OCR Debug: File name:", t.name),
        console.log(" OCR Debug: File size:", t.size, "bytes");
        const e = new FormData;
        e.append("image", t),
        console.log(" OCR Debug: Backend URL:", Xs());
        const r = await fetch(`${Xs()}/ocr`, {
            method: "POST",
            body: e
        });
        if (console.log(" OCR Debug: Response status:", r.status),
        !r.ok) {
            let i = "OCR processing failed";
            const a = r.headers.get("content-type");
            if (a && a.includes("application/json"))
                try {
                    i = (await r.json()).error || i
                } catch (o) {
                    console.error(" OCR Debug: Failed to parse JSON error response:", o),
                    i = `OCR error (${r.status}): Invalid response format`
                }
            else
                try {
                    const o = await r.text();
                    console.error(" OCR Debug: Error response:", o.substring(0, 200)),
                    r.status === 500 ? i = "OCR service is temporarily unavailable. Please try again in a few minutes." : r.status === 404 ? i = "OCR endpoint not found. Please check if the backend is running." : i = `OCR error (${r.status}): ${o.substring(0, 100)}`
                } catch (o) {
                    console.error(" OCR Debug: Failed to read error response:", o),
                    i = `OCR error (${r.status}): Unable to read error details`
                }
            throw new Error(i)
        }
        const n = await r.json();
        return console.log(" OCR Debug: OCR successful"),
        console.log(" OCR Debug: Extracted text length:", n.text ? n.text.length : 0),
        n
    } catch (e) {
        throw console.error(" OCR Debug: Error processing OCR:", e),
        e
    }
}
  , XW = async t => {
    try {
        console.log(" File Debug: Starting file processing"),
        console.log(" File Debug: File name:", t.name),
        console.log(" File Debug: File size:", t.size, "bytes");
        const e = "/file-to-text"
          , r = new FormData;
        r.append("file", t),
        console.log(" File Debug: Using endpoint:", e);
        const n = await fetch(`${Xs()}${e}`, {
            method: "POST",
            body: r
        });
        if (console.log(" File Debug: Response status:", n.status),
        !n.ok) {
            let a = "File processing failed";
            const o = n.headers.get("content-type");
            if (o && o.includes("application/json"))
                try {
                    a = (await n.json()).error || a
                } catch (c) {
                    console.error(" File Debug: Failed to parse JSON error response:", c),
                    a = `File processing error (${n.status}): Invalid response format`
                }
            else
                try {
                    const c = await n.text();
                    console.error(" File Debug: Error response:", c.substring(0, 200)),
                    n.status === 500 ? a = "File processing service is temporarily unavailable. Please try again in a few minutes." : n.status === 404 ? a = "File processing endpoint not found. Please check if the backend is running." : a = `File processing error (${n.status}): ${c.substring(0, 100)}`
                } catch (c) {
                    console.error(" File Debug: Failed to read error response:", c),
                    a = `File processing error (${n.status}): Unable to read error details`
                }
            throw new Error(a)
        }
        const i = await n.json();
        return console.log(" File Debug: File processing successful"),
        console.log(" File Debug: Extracted text length:", i.text ? i.text.length : 0),
        i
    } catch (e) {
        throw console.error(" File Debug: Error processing file:", e),
        e
    }
}
  , JW = () => {
    const [t,e] = O.useState(!1)
      , [r,n] = O.useState(null);

        askQuestion: O.useCallback(async a => {
            e(!0),
            n(null);
            try {
                const o = await fetch(`${Xs()}/ask`, {
                    method: "POST",
                    headers: {
                        "Content-Type": "application/json"
                    },
                    body: JSON.stringify({
                        question: a
                    })
                });
                if (!o.ok) {
                    const u = await o.json();
                    throw new Error(u.error || `HTTP error! status: ${o.status}`)
                }
                return await o.json()
            } catch (o) {
                throw n(o.message),
                o
            } finally {
                e(!1)
            }
        }
        , []),
        loading: t,
        error: r
    }
}
  , QW = async t => {

            body: JSON.stringify(t)
        });

            throw new Error(n.error || `HTTP error! status: ${e.status}`)

    } catch (e) {

    }

function ZW({open: t, onClose: e, onFeedbackSubmitted: r}) {

      , w = async y => {
        if (y.preventDefault(),
        i === 0) {
            alert("Please select a rating");
            return
        }
        m(!0);
        try {
            const P = await QW({
                rating: i,
                feedback: o,
                email: u || n?.email,

                        api_calls_today: E,

            , 2e3)

const e9 = {
    free: 10,
    starter: 25,
    pro: 25
}
  , t9 = {
    free: 50,
    starter: 200,
    pro: 200
};
function r9() {
    const [t,e] = O.useState({
        count: 0,
        limit: 10,
        plan: "free",
        monthlyCount: 0,
        monthlyLimit: 50
    })
      , [r,n] = O.useState(null)
      , [i,a] = O.useState(!1)
      , [o,c] = O.useState(!1)
      , [u,d] = O.useState(!1)
      , p = O.useRef(null)
      , m = O.useRef(0)
      , g = O.useRef(0)
      , b = O.useCallback(async (P, S) => {
        try {
            const {data: {session: j}, error: k} = await Gr.auth.getSession();
            if (k || !j) {
                console.log("No active session found, skipping backend persistence");
                return
            }
            if (r) {
                const E = new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 7)
                  , {data: C, error: N} = await Nt.getProfile(r.id);
                if (!C && !N) {
                    const {error: R} = await Nt.createProfile(r.id, r.email, r.user_metadata?.username, r.user_metadata?.full_name);
                    if (R) {
                        console.error("Failed to create user profile for usage tracking:", R);
                        return
                    }
                }
                const {error: I} = await Nt.updateProfile(r.id, {
                    api_calls_today: P,
                    last_api_call_date: S,
                    api_calls_monthly: t.monthlyCount + 1,
                    last_api_call_month: E
                });
                I ? console.error("Failed to persist API usage:", I) : g.current = P
            }
        } catch (j) {
            console.error("Failed to persist API usage:", j)
        }
    }
    , [r, t.monthlyCount])
      , w = O.useCallback(async () => {
        try {
            const {data: {session: P}, error: S} = await Gr.auth.getSession();
            if (S) {
                console.error("Error getting session:", S);
                const H = new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0]
                  , W = JSON.parse(sessionStorage.getItem("anonUsage") || "{}");
                let Y = W.count || 0;
                W.date !== H && (Y = 0),
                e({
                    count: Y,
                    limit: 10,
                    plan: "free"
                }),
                sessionStorage.setItem("anonUsage", JSON.stringify({
                    count: Y,
                    date: H
                }));
                return
            }
            if (!P) {
                console.log("No active session found, using anonymous usage");
                const H = new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0]
                  , W = JSON.parse(sessionStorage.getItem("anonUsage") || "{}");
                let Y = W.count || 0;
                W.date !== H && (Y = 0),
                e({
                    count: Y,
                    limit: 10,
                    plan: "free"
                }),
                sessionStorage.setItem("anonUsage", JSON.stringify({
                    count: Y,
                    date: H
                }));
                return
            }
            const {user: j, error: k} = await Yn.getCurrentUser();
            if (k) {
                console.error("Error getting current user:", k);
                const H = new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0]
                  , W = JSON.parse(sessionStorage.getItem("anonUsage") || "{}");
                let Y = W.count || 0;
                W.date !== H && (Y = 0),
                e({
                    count: Y,
                    limit: 10,
                    plan: "free"
                }),
                sessionStorage.setItem("anonUsage", JSON.stringify({
                    count: Y,
                    date: H
                }));
                return
            }
            n(j);
            const {data: E, error: C} = await Nt.getProfile(j.id);
            let N = E;
            if (!E && !C) {
                console.log("Creating user profile for:", j.id);
                const {data: H, error: W} = await Nt.createProfile(j.id, j.email, j.user_metadata?.username, j.user_metadata?.full_name);
                W ? (console.error("Error creating user profile:", W),
                N = null) : N = H
            } else
                C && (console.error("Error getting user profile:", C),
                N = null);
            const I = new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0]
              , R = new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 7)
              , U = N?.plan_type || "free"
              , M = e9[U]
              , $ = t9[U];
            let F = N?.api_calls_today || 0
              , G = N?.api_calls_monthly || 0;
            if (N?.last_api_call_date !== I) {
                F = 0;
                const {error: H} = await Nt.updateProfile(j.id, {
                    api_calls_today: 0,
                    last_api_call_date: I
                });
                H && console.error("Failed to reset daily usage count:", H)
            }
            if (N?.last_api_call_month !== R) {
                G = 0;
                const {error: H} = await Nt.updateProfile(j.id, {
                    api_calls_monthly: 0,
                    last_api_call_month: R
                });
                H && console.error("Failed to reset monthly usage count:", H)
            }
            e({
                count: F,
                limit: M,
                plan: U,
                monthlyCount: G,
                monthlyLimit: $
            }),
            g.current = F,
            m.current = F
        } catch (P) {
            console.error("Error loading usage:", P);
            const S = new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0]
              , j = JSON.parse(sessionStorage.getItem("anonUsage") || "{}");
            let k = j.count || 0;
            j.date !== S && (k = 0),
            e({
                count: k,
                limit: 10,
                plan: "free"
            }),
            sessionStorage.setItem("anonUsage", JSON.stringify({
                count: k,
                date: S
            }))
        }
    }
    , []);
    O.useEffect( () => (w(),
    () => {
        p.current && clearTimeout(p.current)
    }
    ), [w]);
    const x = O.useCallback(async () => {
        const P = new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0];
        if (t.count >= t.limit) {
            if (t.plan === "free" && r && r.id) {
                const {data: k, error: E} = await Nt.getProfile(r.id);
                if (!E && k) {
                    const C = k.last_feedback
                      , N = new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0];
                    if (!C || C.split("T")[0] !== N)
                        return c(!0),
                        !1
                }
            } else if (t.plan === "free" && (!r || !r.id)) {
                const k = `You've reached your daily limit of ${t.limit} API calls!

 Sign in or create a free account to:
 Get 5 bonus API calls
 Track your usage
 Save your API history
 Access premium features

Create an account now to continue using Talkapi!`;
                return alert(k),
                a(!0),
                !1
            }
            return a(!0),
            !1
        }
        if (t.monthlyCount >= t.monthlyLimit)
            return a(!0),
            !1;
        const S = t.count + 1
          , j = t.monthlyCount + 1;
        if (e(k => ({
            ...k,
            count: S,
            monthlyCount: j
        })),
        r)
            m.current = S,
            p.current && clearTimeout(p.current),
            p.current = setTimeout( () => {
                m.current > g.current && b(m.current, P)
            }
            , 1e3);
        else
            try {
                sessionStorage.setItem("anonUsage", JSON.stringify({
                    count: S,
                    date: P
                }))
            } catch (k) {
                console.error("Failed to store anonymous API usage:", k)
            }
        return S >= t.limit * .8 && S < t.limit && alert(`Warning: You've used ${S} of ${t.limit} daily API calls. Consider upgrading your plan.`),
        j >= t.monthlyLimit * .8 && j < t.monthlyLimit && alert(`Warning: You've used ${j} of ${t.monthlyLimit} monthly API calls. Consider upgrading your plan.`),
        !0
    }
    , [t, r, b])
      , y = O.useCallback( () => {
        w(),
        c(!1)
    }
    , [w]);
    return {
        usage: t,
        trackApiCall: x,
        showUpgradeModal: i,
        setShowUpgradeModal: a,
        showFeedbackPopup: o,
        setShowFeedbackPopup: c,
        handleFeedbackSubmitted: y,
        loadUsage: w
    }
}
const We = O.forwardRef( ({className: t, ...e}, r) => f.jsx("div", {
    ref: r,
    className: Ce("rounded-xl border bg-card text-card-foreground shadow", t),
    ...e
}));
We.displayName = "Card";

Please try again." : e.includes("invalid url") ? "Invalid URL provided. Please check the URL format." : e.includes("rate limit") || e.includes("429") ? "Too many requests. Please wait a moment before trying again." : "Something went wrong. Please try again."
}

        }

    }

function xA(t, [e,r]) {
    return Math.min(r, Math.max(e, t))

const y9 = ["top", "right", "bottom", "left"]
  , Ta = Math.min
  , Kr = Math.max
  , Zf = Math.round
  , Pf = Math.floor
  , Zn = t => ({
    x: t,
    y: t
})
  , x9 = {
    left: "right",
    right: "left",
    bottom: "top",
    top: "bottom"
}
  , b9 = {
    start: "end",
    end: "start"
};
function Jb(t, e, r) {
    return Kr(t, Ta(e, r))
}
function Ii(t, e) {
    return typeof t == "function" ? t(e) : t
}
function Ri(t) {
    return t.split("-")[0]
}
function Pl(t) {
    return t.split("-")[1]
}
function u_(t) {
    return t === "x" ? "y" : "x"
}
function d_(t) {
    return t === "y" ? "height" : "width"
}
const w9 = new Set(["top", "bottom"]);

    return w9.has(Ri(t)) ? "y" : "x"
}
function f_(t) {
    return u_(Gn(t))
}
function _9(t, e, r) {
    r === void 0 && (r = !1);
    const n = Pl(t)
      , i = f_(t)
      , a = d_(i);
    let o = i === "x" ? n === (r ? "end" : "start") ? "right" : "left" : n === "start" ? "bottom" : "top";
    return e.reference[a] > e.floating[a] && (o = eh(o)),
    [o, eh(o)]
}
function S9(t) {

    return [Qb(t), e, Qb(e)]
}
function Qb(t) {
    return t.replace(/start|end/g, e => b9[e])
}
const bA = ["left", "right"]
  , wA = ["right", "left"]
  , j9 = ["top", "bottom"]
  , P9 = ["bottom", "top"];
function O9(t, e, r) {
    switch (t) {
    case "top":
    case "bottom":
        return r ? e ? wA : bA : e ? bA : wA;
    case "left":
    case "right":
        return e ? j9 : P9;
    default:
        return []
    }
}
function A9(t, e, r, n) {
    const i = Pl(t);
    let a = O9(Ri(t), r === "start", n);
    return i && (a = a.map(o => o + "-" + i),
    e && (a = a.concat(a.map(Qb)))),
    a
}
function eh(t) {
    return t.replace(/left|right|bottom|top/g, e => x9[e])
}
function E9(t) {
    return {
        top: 0,
        right: 0,
        bottom: 0,
        left: 0,

    }
}

    }
}
function th(t) {
    const {x: e, y: r, width: n, height: i} = t;
    return {
        width: n,
        height: i,
        top: r,
        left: e,
        right: e + n,
        bottom: r + i,
        x: e,
        y: r
    }
}
function _A(t, e, r) {
    let {reference: n, floating: i} = t;
    const a = Gn(e)
      , o = f_(e)
      , c = d_(o)
      , u = Ri(e)
      , d = a === "y"
      , p = n.x + n.width / 2 - i.width / 2
      , m = n.y + n.height / 2 - i.height / 2
      , g = n[c] / 2 - i[c] / 2;
    let b;
    switch (u) {
    case "top":
        b = {
            x: p,
            y: n.y - i.height
        };
        break;
    case "bottom":
        b = {
            x: p,
            y: n.y + n.height
        };
        break;
    case "right":
        b = {
            x: n.x + n.width,
            y: m
        };
        break;
    case "left":
        b = {
            x: n.x - i.width,
            y: m
        };
        break;
    default:
        b = {
            x: n.x,
            y: n.y
        }
    }
    switch (Pl(e)) {
    case "start":
        b[o] -= g * (r && d ? -1 : 1);
        break;
    case "end":
        b[o] += g * (r && d ? -1 : 1);
        break
    }
    return b
}
const k9 = async (t, e, r) => {
    const {placement: n="bottom", strategy: i="absolute", middleware: a=[], platform: o} = r
      , c = a.filter(Boolean)
      , u = await (o.isRTL == null ? void 0 : o.isRTL(e));
    let d = await o.getElementRects({
        reference: t,
        floating: e,
        strategy: i
    })
      , {x: p, y: m} = _A(d, n, u)
      , g = n
      , b = {}
      , w = 0;
    for (let x = 0; x < c.length; x++) {
        const {name: y, fn: P} = c[x]
          , {x: S, y: j, data: k, reset: E} = await P({
            x: p,
            y: m,
            initialPlacement: n,
            placement: g,
            strategy: i,
            middlewareData: b,
            rects: d,
            platform: o,

const jD = Math.cos
  , ah = Math.sin
  , Mn = Math.sqrt

function PD(t) {
    this._ += t[0];
    for (let e = 1, r = t.length; e < r; ++e)
        this._ += arguments[e] + t[e]
}
function $V(t) {

    if (!(e >= 0))
        throw new Error(`invalid digits: ${t}`);
    if (e > 15)
        return PD;
    const r = 10 ** e;
    return function(n) {
        this._ += n[0];
        for (let i = 1, a = n.length; i < a; ++i)
            this._ += Math.round(arguments[i] * r) / r + n[i]
    }

class DV {
    constructor(e) {
        this._x0 = this._y0 = this._x1 = this._y1 = null,
        this._ = "",
        this._append = e == null ? PD : $V(e)
    }
    moveTo(e, r) {
        this._append`M${this._x0 = this._x1 = +e},${this._y0 = this._y1 = +r}`
    }
    closePath() {
        this._x1 !== null && (this._x1 = this._x0,
        this._y1 = this._y0,
        this._append`Z`)
    }
    lineTo(e, r) {
        this._append`L${this._x1 = +e},${this._y1 = +r}`
    }
    quadraticCurveTo(e, r, n, i) {
        this._append`Q${+e},${+r},${this._x1 = +n},${this._y1 = +i}`
    }
    bezierCurveTo(e, r, n, i, a, o) {
        this._append`C${+e},${+r},${+n},${+i},${this._x1 = +a},${this._y1 = +o}`
    }
    arcTo(e, r, n, i, a) {
        if (e = +e,
        r = +r,
        n = +n,
        i = +i,
        a = +a,
        a < 0)
            throw new Error(`negative radius: ${a}`);
        let o = this._x1
          , c = this._y1
          , u = n - e
          , d = i - r
          , p = o - e
          , m = c - r
          , g = p * p + m * m;
        if (this._x1 === null)
            this._append`M${this._x1 = e},${this._y1 = r}`;
        else if (g > fo)
            if (!(Math.abs(m * u - d * p) > fo) || !a)
                this._append`L${this._x1 = e},${this._y1 = r}`;
            else {
                let b = n - o
                  , w = i - c
                  , x = u * u + d * d
                  , y = b * b + w * w
                  , P = Math.sqrt(x)
                  , S = Math.sqrt(g)
                  , j = a * Math.tan((dw - Math.acos((x + g - y) / (2 * P * S))) / 2)
                  , k = j / S
                  , E = j / P;
                Math.abs(k - 1) > fo && this._append`L${e + k * p},${r + k * m}`,
                this._append`A${a},${a},0,0,${+(m * b > p * w)},${this._x1 = e + E * u},${this._y1 = r + E * d}`
            }
    }
    arc(e, r, n, i, a, o) {
        if (e = +e,
        r = +r,
        n = +n,
        o = !!o,
        n < 0)
            throw new Error(`negative radius: ${n}`);
        let c = n * Math.cos(i)
          , u = n * Math.sin(i)
          , d = e + c
          , p = r + u
          , m = 1 ^ o
          , g = o ? i - a : a - i;
        this._x1 === null ? this._append`M${d},${p}` : (Math.abs(this._x1 - d) > fo || Math.abs(this._y1 - p) > fo) && this._append`L${d},${p}`,
        n && (g < 0 && (g = g % fw + fw),
        g > MV ? this._append`A${n},${n},0,1,${m},${e - c},${r - u}A${n},${n},0,1,${m},${this._x1 = d},${this._y1 = p}` : g > fo && this._append`A${n},${n},0,${+(g >= dw)},${m},${this._x1 = e + n * Math.cos(a)},${this._y1 = r + n * Math.sin(a)}`)
    }
    rect(e, r, n, i) {
        this._append`M${this._x0 = this._x1 = +e},${this._y0 = this._y1 = +r}h${n = +n}v${+i}h${-n}Z`
    }
    toString() {
        return this._
    }
}

    }

    () => new DV(e)
}

class CD {

        this._point = 0
    }

        (this._line || this._line !== 0 && this._point === 1) && this._context.closePath(),
        this._line = 1 - this._line
    }
    point(e, r) {
        switch (e = +e,
        r = +r,
        this._point) {
        case 0:
            {
                this._point = 1,
                this._line ? this._context.lineTo(e, r) : this._context.moveTo(e, r);
                break

                this._x ? this._context.bezierCurveTo(this._x0 = (this._x0 + e) / 2, this._y0, this._x0, r, e, r) : this._context.bezierCurveTo(this._x0, this._y0 = (this._y0 + r) / 2, e, this._y0, e, r);

        this._y0 = r
    }

function YE(t) {
    return t < 0 ? -1 : 1
}
function XE(t, e, r) {
    var n = t._x1 - t._x0
      , i = e - t._x1
      , a = (t._y1 - t._y0) / (n || i < 0 && -0)
      , o = (r - t._y1) / (i || n < 0 && -0)
      , c = (a * i + o * n) / (n + i);
    return (YE(a) + YE(o)) * Math.min(Math.abs(a), Math.abs(o), .5 * Math.abs(c)) || 0
}
function JE(t, e) {
    var r = t._x1 - t._x0;
    return r ? (3 * (t._y1 - t._y0) / r - e) / 2 : e
}
function My(t, e, r) {
    var n = t._x0
      , i = t._y0
      , a = t._x1
      , o = t._y1
      , c = (a - n) / 3;
    t._context.bezierCurveTo(n + c, i + c * e, a - c, o - c * r, a, o)
}
function ch(t) {
    this._context = t
}
ch.prototype = {
    areaStart: function() {
        this._line = 0
    },

        case 2:
            this._context.lineTo(this._x1, this._y1);

            break

        (this._line || this._line !== 0 && this._point === 1) && this._context.closePath(),
        this._line = 1 - this._line
    },

        if (t = +t,
        e = +e,
        !(t === this._x1 && e === this._y1)) {
            switch (this._point) {
            case 0:
                this._point = 1,
                this._line ? this._context.lineTo(t, e) : this._context.moveTo(t, e);
                break;
            case 1:
                this._point = 2;
                break;

function UD(t) {

    areaStart: function() {

    },
    areaEnd: function() {
        this._line = NaN
    },

        this._y = []
    },

          , e = this._y
          , r = t.length;
        if (r)
            if (this._line ? this._context.lineTo(t[0], e[0]) : this._context.moveTo(t[0], e[0]),
            r === 2)
                this._context.lineTo(t[1], e[1]);
            else
                for (var n = QE(t), i = QE(e), a = 0, o = 1; o < r; ++a,
                ++o)
                    this._context.bezierCurveTo(n[0][a], i[0][a], n[1][a], i[1][a], t[o], e[o]);
        (this._line || this._line !== 0 && r === 1) && this._context.closePath(),
        this._line = 1 - this._line,
        this._x = this._y = null
    },

        this._x.push(+t),
        this._y.push(+e)
    }

function QE(t) {
    var e, r = t.length - 1, n, i = new Array(r), a = new Array(r), o = new Array(r);
    for (i[0] = 0,
    a[0] = 2,
    o[0] = t[0] + 2 * t[1],
    e = 1; e < r - 1; ++e)
        i[e] = 1,
        a[e] = 4,
        o[e] = 4 * t[e] + 2 * t[e + 1];
    for (i[r - 1] = 2,
    a[r - 1] = 7,
    o[r - 1] = 8 * t[r - 1] + t[r],
    e = 1; e < r; ++e)
        n = i[e] / a[e - 1],
        a[e] -= n,
        o[e] -= n * o[e - 1];
    for (i[r - 1] = o[r - 1] / a[r - 1],
    e = r - 2; e >= 0; --e)
        i[e] = (o[e] - i[e + 1]) / a[e];
    for (a[r - 1] = (t[r] + i[r - 1]) / 2,
    e = 0; e < r - 1; ++e)
        a[e] = 2 * t[e + 1] - i[e + 1];
    return [i, a]
}

function Tp(t, e) {
    this._context = t,
    this._t = e
}
Tp.prototype = {
    areaStart: function() {
        this._line = 0
    },
    areaEnd: function() {
        this._line = NaN
    },
    lineStart: function() {
        this._x = this._y = NaN,
        this._point = 0
    },
    lineEnd: function() {
        0 < this._t && this._t < 1 && this._point === 2 && this._context.lineTo(this._x, this._y),
        (this._line || this._line !== 0 && this._point === 1) && this._context.closePath(),
        this._line >= 0 && (this._t = 1 - this._t,
        this._line = 1 - this._line)
    },
    point: function(t, e) {
        switch (t = +t,
        e = +e,
        this._point) {
        case 0:
            this._point = 1,
            this._line ? this._context.lineTo(t, e) : this._context.moveTo(t, e);
            break;
        case 1:
            this._point = 2;
        default:
            {
                if (this._t <= 0)
                    this._context.lineTo(this._x, e),
                    this._context.lineTo(t, e);
                else {
                    var r = this._x * (1 - this._t) + t * this._t;
                    this._context.lineTo(r, this._y),
                    this._context.lineTo(r, e)
                }
                break
            }
        }

function $L() {

function UL(t, e, r, n, i, a) {
    const o = [[wo, 1, Oi], [wo, 5, 5 * Oi], [wo, 15, 15 * Oi], [wo, 30, 30 * Oi], [a, 1, fn], [a, 5, 5 * fn], [a, 15, 15 * fn], [a, 30, 30 * fn], [i, 1, Ai], [i, 3, 3 * Ai], [i, 6, 6 * Ai], [i, 12, 12 * Ai], [n, 1, Mi], [n, 2, 2 * Mi], [r, 1, eS], [e, 1, GN], [e, 3, 3 * GN], [t, 1, Tx]];
    function c(d, p, m) {
        const g = p < d;
        g && ([d,p] = [p, d]);
        const b = m && typeof m.range == "function" ? m : u(d, p, m)
          , w = b ? b.range(d, +p + 1) : [];
        return g ? w.reverse() : w
    }

          , b = q_( ([,,y]) => y).right(o, g);

    }

    function C(ne, fe) {
        return function(pe) {
            var te = [], Ue = -1, ke = 0, pt = ne.length, mt, Et, Lr;
            for (pe instanceof Date || (pe = new Date(+pe)); ++Ue < pt; )
                ne.charCodeAt(Ue) === 37 && (te.push(ne.slice(ke, Ue)),
                (Et = KN[mt = ne.charAt(++Ue)]) != null ? mt = ne.charAt(++Ue) : Et = mt === "e" ? " " : "0",

                te.push(mt),

            te.join("")
        }
    }
    function N(ne, fe) {
        return function(pe) {
            var te = jc(1900, void 0, 1), Ue = I(te, ne, pe += "", 0), ke, pt;
            if (Ue != pe.length)
                return null;
            if ("Q"in te)

                ("W"in te || "U"in te) && ("w"in te || (te.w = "u"in te ? te.u % 7 : "W"in te ? 1 : 0),
                pt = "Z"in te ? Rx(jc(te.y, 0, 1)).getUTCDay() : Ix(jc(te.y, 0, 1)).getDay(),

            te.M += te.Z % 100,
            Rx(te)) : Ix(te)
        }
    }
    function I(ne, fe, pe, te) {
        for (var Ue = 0, ke = fe.length, pt = pe.length, mt, Et; Ue < ke; ) {
            if (te >= pt)
                return -1;

            mt === 37) {

                Et = E[mt in KN ? fe.charAt(Ue++) : mt],
                !Et || (te = Et(ne, pe, te)) < 0)
                    return -1
            } else if (mt != pe.charCodeAt(te++))
                return -1
        }
        return te
    }
    function R(ne, fe, pe) {
        var te = d.exec(fe.slice(pe));
        return te ? (ne.p = p.get(te[0].toLowerCase()),
        pe + te[0].length) : -1

        pe + te[0].length) : -1

    function Y(ne) {

    }
    function K(ne) {

    }

    }

            }
            ,
            fe
        }
    }

var KN = {
    "-": "",
    _: " ",
    0: "0"
}
  , ir = /^\s*\d+/
  , QJ = /^%/
  , ZJ = /[\\^$*+?|[\]().{}]/g;
function it(t, e, r) {
    var n = t < 0 ? "-" : ""
      , i = (n ? -t : t) + ""
      , a = i.length;
    return n + (a < r ? new Array(r - a + 1).join(e) + i : i)
}
function eQ(t) {
    return t.replace(ZJ, "\\$&")
}
function Pc(t) {
    return new RegExp("^(?:" + t.map(eQ).join("|") + ")","i")
}
function Oc(t) {
    return new Map(t.map( (e, r) => [e.toLowerCase(), r]))
}

function i4(t, e) {

            Ee(E, "handleTouchEnd", function(C) {

            x("Failed to load admin data. Please try again.")
        } finally {
            b(!1)
        }

      , P = async (I, R, U=null) => {
        try {
            switch (R) {
            case "disable":
                await User.update(I, {
                    status: "disabled"
                }),
                alert("User account disabled");
                break;
            case "upgrade":
                await User.update(I, {
                    plan: U
                }),
                alert(`User upgraded to ${U} plan`);
                break;
            case "makeAdmin":
                await User.update(I, {
                    role: U ? "admin" : "user"
                }),
                alert(`User admin status ${U ? "granted" : "revoked"}`);
                break;
            case "resetUsage":
                await User.update(I, {
                    apiCallsToday: 0,
                    lastApiCallDate: new Date().toISOString().split("T")[0]
                }),
                alert("User daily usage reset");
                break;
            case "delete":
                confirm("Are you sure you want to permanently delete this user?") && (await User.delete(I),
                alert("User deleted permanently"));
                break
            }
            await y()
        } catch (M) {
            alert("Action failed: " + M.message)
        }
    }

    free: {
        name: "Free",
        price: "$0/month",
        color: "bg-gray-600",
        features: ["10 API calls/day", "25 API calls/month", "1 week history", "Basic email support"]
    }

function U3() {
    const [t,e] = O.useState(null)
      , [r,n] = O.useState([])
      , [i,a] = O.useState([])
      , [o,c] = O.useState(!0)
      , [u,d] = O.useState(!0)
      , {usage: p, loadUsage: m} = HW();
    if (O.useEffect( () => {
        (async () => {
            try {
                const {user: y, error: P} = await Yn.getCurrentUser();
                if (P) {
                    console.error("Error getting current user:", P),
                    window.location.href = ot("Login");
                    return
                }
                e(y),
                await m(),
                d(!0);
                try {
                    n([]),
                    a([])
                } catch (S) {
                    console.error("Failed to load history:", S),
                    n([]),
                    a([])
                } finally {
                    d(!1)
                }
            } catch (y) {
                console.error("Error loading account data:", y),
                window.location.href = ot("Login")
            } finally {
                c(!1)
            }
        }
        )()
    }
    , [m]),
    o)
        return f.jsx("div", {
            className: "flex items-center justify-center min-h-screen",
            children: f.jsxs("div", {
                className: "text-center",
                children: [f.jsx("div", {
                    className: "animate-spin rounded-full h-12 w-12 border-b-2 border-white mx-auto mb-4"
                }), f.jsx("p", {
                    className: "text-gray-300",
                    children: "Loading your account..."
                })]
            })
        });
    if (!t)
        return f.jsx("div", {
            className: "flex items-center justify-center min-h-screen",
            children: f.jsx(Jn, {
                className: "max-w-md bg-red-900/20 border-red-500",
                children: f.jsx(Qn, {
                    className: "text-red-300",
                    children: "Please sign in to view your account."
                })
            })
        });
    const g = Hce.free
      , b = vo(new Date(t.created_at), "MMMM dd, yyyy")
      , w = x => x.length > 0 ? f.jsx("div", {

async function Vce(t) {
    const e = "https://askapi-dev.onrender.com"
      , r = new URLSearchParams({
        sum: t
    })
      , n = await fetch(`${e}/payment/token?${r}`, {
        method: "POST",
        headers: {
            "Content-Type": "application/json"
        }
    })
      , i = await n.json();
    if (console.log(" ~ getHandshakeToken ~ response status and data:", n.status, i),
    !n.ok || i.status === "error")
        throw new Error(i.message || "Failed to get handshake token");
    return i
}
