const Gce = ({status: t, label: e, description: r, lastChecked: n}) => {
    const a = (c => {
        switch (c) {
        case "operational":
            return {
                icon: Oa,
                color: "text-green-400",
                bgColor: "bg-green-600",
                textColor: "text-green-100"
            };
        case "degraded":
            return {
                icon: Ca,
                color: "text-yellow-400",
                bgColor: "bg-yellow-600",
                textColor: "text-yellow-100"
            };
        case "outage":
            return {
                icon: tR,
                color: "text-red-400",
                bgColor: "bg-red-600",
                textColor: "text-red-100"
            };
        default:
            return {
                icon: GI,
                color: "text-gray-400",
                bgColor: "bg-gray-600",
                textColor: "text-gray-100"
            }
        }
    }
    )(t)
      , o = a.icon;
    return f.jsxs("div", {
        className: "flex items-center justify-between p-4 bg-slate-800/30 rounded-lg",
        children: [f.jsxs("div", {
            className: "flex items-center gap-3",
            children: [f.jsx(o, {
                className: `w-5 h-5 ${a.color}`
            }), f.jsxs("div", {
                children: [f.jsx("h3", {
                    className: "text-white font-medium",
                    children: e
                }), f.jsx("p", {
                    className: "text-gray-400 text-sm",
                    children: r
                })]
            })]
        }), f.jsxs("div", {
            className: "text-right",
            children: [f.jsx(xr, {
                className: `${a.bgColor} ${a.textColor} mb-1`,
                children: t.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + t.slice(1)
            }), f.jsxs("p", {
                className: "text-gray-500 text-xs",
                children: ["Updated ", n]
            })]
        })]
    })
}

var dm = "Checkbox"
  , [Kce,Sue] = ai(dm)
  , [Yce,jS] = Kce(dm);
function Xce(t) {
    const {__scopeCheckbox: e, checked: r, children: n, defaultChecked: i, disabled: a, form: o, name: c, onCheckedChange: u, required: d, value: p="on", internal_do_not_use_render: m} = t
      , [g,b] = Ti({
        prop: r,
        defaultProp: i ?? !1,
        onChange: u,
        caller: dm
    })
      , [w,x] = O.useState(null)
      , [y,P] = O.useState(null)
      , S = O.useRef(!1)
      , j = w ? !!o || !!w.closest("form") : !0
      , k = {
        checked: g,
        disabled: a,
        setChecked: b,
        control: w,
        setControl: x,
        name: c,
        form: o,
        value: p,
        hasConsumerStoppedPropagationRef: S,
        required: d,
        defaultChecked: ka(i) ? !1 : i,
        isFormControl: j,
        bubbleInput: y,
        setBubbleInput: P
    };
    return f.jsx(Yce, {
        scope: e,
        ...k,
        children: Jce(m) ? m(k) : n
    })
}
var W3 = "CheckboxTrigger"
  , H3 = O.forwardRef( ({__scopeCheckbox: t, onKeyDown: e, onClick: r, ...n}, i) => {
    const {control: a, value: o, disabled: c, checked: u, required: d, setControl: p, setChecked: m, hasConsumerStoppedPropagationRef: g, isFormControl: b, bubbleInput: w} = jS(W3, t)
      , x = St(i, p)
      , y = O.useRef(u);
    return O.useEffect( () => {
        const P = a?.form;
        if (P) {
            const S = () => m(y.current);
            return P.addEventListener("reset", S),
            () => P.removeEventListener("reset", S)
        }
    }
    , [a, m]),
    f.jsx(Fe.button, {
        type: "button",
        role: "checkbox",
        "aria-checked": ka(u) ? "mixed" : u,
        "aria-required": d,
        "data-state": X3(u),
        "data-disabled": c ? "" : void 0,
        disabled: c,
        value: o,
        ...n,
        ref: x,
        onKeyDown: Qe(e, P => {
            P.key === "Enter" && P.preventDefault()
        }
        ),
        onClick: Qe(r, P => {
            m(S => ka(S) ? !0 : !S),
            w && b && (g.current = P.isPropagationStopped(),
            g.current || P.stopPropagation())
        }
        )
    })
}
);
H3.displayName = W3;
var PS = O.forwardRef( (t, e) => {
    const {__scopeCheckbox: r, name: n, checked: i, defaultChecked: a, required: o, disabled: c, value: u, onCheckedChange: d, form: p, ...m} = t;
    return f.jsx(Xce, {
        __scopeCheckbox: r,
        checked: i,
        defaultChecked: a,
        disabled: c,
        required: o,
        onCheckedChange: d,
        name: n,
        form: p,
        value: u,
        internal_do_not_use_render: ({isFormControl: g}) => f.jsxs(f.Fragment, {
            children: [f.jsx(H3, {
                ...m,
                ref: e,
                __scopeCheckbox: r
            }), g && f.jsx(Y3, {
                __scopeCheckbox: r
            })]
        })
    })
}
);
PS.displayName = dm;
var V3 = "CheckboxIndicator"
  , G3 = O.forwardRef( (t, e) => {

      , a = jS(V3, r);
    return f.jsx(Bo, {
        present: n || ka(a.checked) || a.checked === !0,

            }
        })
    })
}

var K3 = "CheckboxBubbleInput"
  , Y3 = O.forwardRef( ({__scopeCheckbox: t, ...e}, r) => {
    const {control: n, hasConsumerStoppedPropagationRef: i, checked: a, defaultChecked: o, required: c, disabled: u, name: d, value: p, form: m, bubbleInput: g, setBubbleInput: b} = jS(K3, t)
      , w = St(r, b)
      , x = k$(a)
      , y = y$(n);
    O.useEffect( () => {
        const S = g;
        if (!S)
            return;
        const j = window.HTMLInputElement.prototype
          , E = Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(j, "checked").set
          , C = !i.current;
        if (x !== a && E) {
            const N = new Event("click",{
                bubbles: C
            });
            S.indeterminate = ka(a),
            E.call(S, ka(a) ? !1 : a),
            S.dispatchEvent(N)
        }
    }
    , [g, x, a, i]);
    const P = O.useRef(ka(a) ? !1 : a);
    return f.jsx(Fe.input, {
        type: "checkbox",
        "aria-hidden": !0,
        defaultChecked: o ?? P.current,
        required: c,
        disabled: u,
        name: d,
        value: p,
        form: m,
        ...e,
        tabIndex: -1,
        ref: w,
        style: {
            ...e.style,
            ...y,
            position: "absolute",
            pointerEvents: "none",
            opacity: 0,
            margin: 0,
            transform: "translateX(-100%)"
        }
    })
}
);
Y3.displayName = K3;
function Jce(t) {
    return typeof t == "function"
}
function ka(t) {
    return t === "indeterminate"
}
function X3(t) {
    return ka(t) ? "indeterminate" : t ? "checked" : "unchecked"
}

    ...e,

function Z3() {
    const {signUp: t, loading: e, error: r, clearError: n} = Ma()
      , [i,a] = O.useState({
        email: "",
        password: ""
    })
      , [o,c] = O.useState(!1)
      , [u,d] = O.useState("")
      , [p,m] = O.useState({
        score: 0,
        feedback: []
    })
      , g = ii()
      , b = S => {
        const {name: j, value: k} = S.target;
        console.log("Input changed:", {
            name: j,
            value: j === "password" ? "***" + k.slice(-3) : k
        }),
        a(E => ({
            ...E,
            [j]: k
        })),
        j === "password" && w(k),
        (u || r) && (d(""),
        n())
    }
      , w = S => {
        const j = [];
        let k = 0;
        S.length >= 8 && (k += 1,
        j.push("At least 8 characters")),
        /[a-z]/.test(S) && (k += 1,
        j.push("Contains lowercase letter")),
        /[A-Z]/.test(S) && (k += 1,
        j.push("Contains uppercase letter")),
        /[0-9]/.test(S) && (k += 1,
        j.push("Contains number")),
        /[^A-Za-z0-9]/.test(S) && (k += 1,
        j.push("Contains special character")),
        m({
            score: k,
            feedback: j
        })
    }
      , x = () => (console.log("Validating form data:", {
        email: i.email,
        emailLength: i.email?.length || 0,
        password: i.password ? "Yes (length: " + i.password.length + ")" : "No",
        passwordStrength: p.score
    }),
    !i.email || !i.password ? (console.log("Validation failed: Missing email or password"),
    d("Please fill in all required fields."),
    !1) : p.score < 3 ? (console.log("Validation failed: Password too weak (score: " + p.score + ")"),
    d("Password is too weak. Please choose a stronger password."),
    !1) : (console.log("Form validation passed"),
    !0))
      , y = async S => {
        if (S.preventDefault(),
        d(""),
        !x())
            return;
        console.log("Form data being sent to signUp:", {
            email: i.email,
            password: i.password ? "***" + i.password.slice(-3) : "empty"
        });
        const j = await t(i.email, i.password);
        console.log("SignUp result:", j),
        j.success ? g(ot("Home")) : d(j.error || "Registration failed. Please try again.")
    }
      , P = () => p.score >= 4 ? "text-green-400" : p.score >= 3 ? "text-yellow-400" : "text-red-400";
    return f.jsx("div", {
        className: "min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900 via-blue-900 to-purple-900 text-white px-4 sm:px-6 py-8",
        children: f.jsxs("div", {
            className: "w-full max-w-md",
            children: [f.jsxs(Ct, {
                to: ot("Home"),
                className: "inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-blue-200 hover:text-white transition-colors mb-8",
                children: [f.jsx(k1, {
                    className: "w-4 h-4"
                }), "Back to Home"]
            }), f.jsxs("div", {
                className: "bg-black/20 backdrop-blur-lg border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-6 sm:p-8",
                children: [f.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "text-center mb-8",
                    children: [f.jsx("h1", {
                        className: "text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-2",
                        children: "Create Account"
                    }), f.jsx("p", {
                        className: "text-blue-200",
                        children: "Join Talkapi and start building better APIs"
                    })]
                }), (u || r) && f.jsx("div", {
                    className: "mb-6 p-4 bg-red-500/20 border border-red-500/30 rounded-lg text-red-200 text-sm",
                    children: u || r
                }), f.jsxs("form", {
                    onSubmit: y,
                    className: "space-y-6",
                    children: [f.jsxs("div", {
                        className: "space-y-2",
                        children: [f.jsx("label", {
                            htmlFor: "email",
                            className: "text-sm font-medium text-gray-300",
                            children: "Email Address"
                        }), f.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "relative",
                            children: [f.jsx(Po, {
                                className: "absolute left-3 top-1/2 transform -translate-y-1/2 w-4 h-4 text-gray-400"
                            }), f.jsx($r, {
                                id: "email",
                                name: "email",
                                type: "email",
                                value: i.email,
                                onChange: b,
                                placeholder: "Enter your email",

                                required: !0
                            })]
                        })]
                    }), f.jsxs("div", {

                        }), f.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "relative",

                                className: "absolute left-3 top-1/2 transform -translate-y-1/2 w-4 h-4 text-gray-400"
                            }), f.jsx($r, {
                                id: "password",
                                name: "password",
                                type: o ? "text" : "password",
                                value: i.password,
                                onChange: b,
                                placeholder: "Create a strong password",
                                className: "pl-10 pr-10 bg-black/30 border-white/20 text-white placeholder:text-gray-400 focus:border-blue-500 focus:ring-blue-500",
                                required: !0
                            }), f.jsx("button", {
                                type: "button",
                                onClick: () => c(!o),
                                className: "absolute right-3 top-1/2 transform -translate-y-1/2 text-gray-400 hover:text-white transition-colors",
                                children: o ? f.jsx(XI, {
                                    className: "w-4 h-4"
                                }) : f.jsx(JI, {
                                    className: "w-4 h-4"
                                })
                            })]
                        }), i.password && f.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "mt-2",
                            children: [f.jsxs("div", {

                                children: [f.jsx("div", {
                                    className: "flex-1 bg-gray-700 rounded-full h-2",
                                    children: f.jsx("div", {
                                        className: `h-2 rounded-full transition-all duration-300 ${p.score >= 4 ? "bg-green-500" : p.score >= 3 ? "bg-yellow-500" : "bg-red-500"}`,
                                        style: {
                                            width: `${p.score / 5 * 100}%`
                                        }
                                    })
                                }), f.jsx("span", {
                                    className: `text-xs font-medium ${P()}`,
                                    children: p.score >= 4 ? "Strong" : p.score >= 3 ? "Good" : p.score >= 2 ? "Fair" : "Weak"
                                })]

const wi = t => {
    if (!t)
        return "An unexpected error occurred";
    const e = t.toLowerCase();
    return e.includes("user from sub claim in jwt does not exist") ? "Authentication session expired. Please sign in again." : e.includes("unauthorized") || e.includes("401") ? "Session expired. Please sign in again." : e.includes("not found") || e.includes("404") ? "Profile not found. Please try again." : e.includes("network error") || e.includes("fetch") ? "Connection error. Please check your internet connection and try again." : e.includes("internal server error") || e.includes("500") ? "Server error. Please try again later." : "Something went wrong. Please try again."
}
  , nU = () => {
    const [t,e] = O.useState(null)
      , [r,n] = O.useState(!0)
      , [i,a] = O.useState(null)
      , [o,c] = O.useState(null)
      , u = async S => {
        try {
            n(!0),
            a(null);
            const {data: j, error: k} = await Nt.getProfile(S);
            return k ? (console.error("Error fetching profile:", k),
            a(wi(k.message)),
            null) : j
        } catch (j) {
            return console.error("Error in fetchProfile:", j),
            a(wi(j.message)),
            null
        } finally {
            n(!1)
        }
    }
      , d = async (S, j, k=null, E=null) => {
        try {
            n(!0),
            a(null);
            const {data: C, error: N} = await Nt.createProfile(S, j, k, E);
            return N ? (console.error("Error creating profile:", N),
            a(wi(N.message)),
            !1) : (e(C),
            !0)
        } catch (C) {
            return console.error("Error in createProfile:", C),
            a(wi(C.message)),
            !1
        } finally {
            n(!1)
        }
    }
      , p = async S => {
        if (!o?.id)
            return a("No user logged in"),
            !1;
        try {
            n(!0),
            a(null);
            const {data: j, error: k} = await Nt.updateProfile(o.id, S);
            if (k)
                return console.error("Error updating profile:", k),
                a(wi(k.message)),
                !1;
            const E = await u(o.id);
            return e(E),
            !0
        } catch (j) {
            return console.error("Error in updateProfile:", j),
            a(wi(j.message)),
            !1
        } finally {
            n(!1)
        }
    }
    ;
    O.useEffect( () => {
        (async () => {
            try {
                const {data: {session: k}, error: E} = await Gr.auth.getSession();
                if (E) {
                    console.error("Error getting session:", E),
                    a(wi(E.message)),
                    n(!1);
                    return
                }
                if (!k) {
                    console.log("No active session found"),
                    c(null),
                    e(null),
                    n(!1);
                    return
                }
                const {user: C, error: N} = await Yn.getCurrentUser();
                if (N) {
                    const R = N.message?.toLowerCase() || "";
                    R.includes("no session") || R.includes("user from sub claim in jwt does not exist") || R.includes("invalid jwt") ? (console.log("No active user session - this is normal for new users"),
                    c(null),
                    e(null)) : (console.error("Error getting current user:", N),
                    a(wi(N.message))),
                    n(!1);
                    return
                }
                if (!C) {
                    c(null),
                    e(null),
                    n(!1);
                    return
                }
                c(C);
                const I = await u(C.id);
                if (I)
                    e(I);
                else if (await d(C.id, C.email, C.user_metadata?.username, C.user_metadata?.full_name)) {
                    const U = await u(C.id);
                    e(U)
                }
            } catch (k) {
                console.error("Error initializing user:", k),
                a(wi(k.message))
            } finally {
                n(!1)
            }
        }
        )();
        const {data: {subscription: j}} = Yn.onAuthStateChange(async (k, E) => {
            if (k === "SIGNED_IN" && E?.user) {
                c(E.user);
                const C = await u(E.user.id);
                e(C)
            } else
                k === "SIGNED_OUT" && (c(null),
                e(null))
        }
        );
        return () => j?.unsubscribe()
    }
    , []);
    const m = async S => p({
        username: S
    })
      , g = async S => p({
        full_name: S
    })
      , b = async S => p({
        email: S
    })
      , w = async S => p({
        plan_type: S
    })
      , x = async S => p({
        daily_limit: S
    })
      , y = () => t ? {
        planType: t.plan_type || "free",
        dailyLimit: t.daily_limit || 5,
        apiCallsToday: t.api_calls_today || 0,
        remainingCalls: Math.max(0, (t.daily_limit || 5) - (t.api_calls_today || 0)),
        lastApiCallDate: t.last_api_call_date
    } : null;
    return {
        user: o,
        profile: t,
        loading: r,
        error: i,
        createProfile: d,
        updateProfile: p,
        updateUsername: m,
        updateFullName: g,
        updateEmail: b,
        updatePlanType: w,
        updateDailyLimit: x,
        getUsageStats: y,
        canMakeApiCall: () => {
            const S = y();
            return S ? S.remainingCalls > 0 : !1
        }
        ,
        isAuthenticated: !!o,
        hasProfile: !!t,
        username: t?.username,
        fullName: t?.full_name,
        email: t?.email,
        planType: t?.plan_type || "free",
        dailyLimit: t?.daily_limit || 5,
        apiCallsToday: t?.api_calls_today || 0
    }
}

const rue = 20
  , nue = 1e6
  , ki = {
    ADD_TOAST: "ADD_TOAST",
    UPDATE_TOAST: "UPDATE_TOAST",
    DISMISS_TOAST: "DISMISS_TOAST",
    REMOVE_TOAST: "REMOVE_TOAST"
};
let Pb = 0;
function iue() {
    return Pb = (Pb + 1) % Number.MAX_VALUE,
    Pb.toString()
}
const Ob = new Map
  , TI = t => {
    if (Ob.has(t))
        return;
    const e = setTimeout( () => {
        Ob.delete(t),
        Yc({
            type: ki.REMOVE_TOAST,
            toastId: t
        })
    }
    , nue);
    Ob.set(t, e)
}
  , aue = (t, e) => {
    switch (e.type) {
    case ki.ADD_TOAST:
        return {
            ...t,
            toasts: [e.toast, ...t.toasts].slice(0, rue)
        };
    case ki.UPDATE_TOAST:
        return {
            ...t,
            toasts: t.toasts.map(r => r.id === e.toast.id ? {
                ...r,
                ...e.toast
            } : r)
        };
    case ki.DISMISS_TOAST:
        {
            const {toastId: r} = e;
            return r ? TI(r) : t.toasts.forEach(n => {
                TI(n.id)
            }
            ),
            {
                ...t,
                toasts: t.toasts.map(n => n.id === r || r === void 0 ? {
                    ...n,
                    open: !1
                } : n)
            }
        }
    case ki.REMOVE_TOAST:
        return e.toastId === void 0 ? {
            ...t,
            toasts: []
        } : {
            ...t,
            toasts: t.toasts.filter(r => r.id !== e.toastId)
        }
    }
}
  , Hf = [];
let Vf = {
    toasts: []
};
function Yc(t) {
    Vf = aue(Vf, t),
    Hf.forEach(e => {
        e(Vf)
    }
    )
}
function oue({...t}) {
    const e = iue()
      , r = i => Yc({
        type: ki.UPDATE_TOAST,
        toast: {
            ...i,
            id: e
        }
    })
      , n = () => Yc({
        type: ki.DISMISS_TOAST,
        toastId: e
    });
    return Yc({
        type: ki.ADD_TOAST,
        toast: {
            ...t,
            id: e,
            open: !0,
            onOpenChange: i => {
                i || n()
            }
        }
    }),
    {
        id: e,
        dismiss: n,
        update: r
    }
}
function sue() {
    const [t,e] = O.useState(Vf);
    return O.useEffect( () => (Hf.push(e),
    () => {
        const r = Hf.indexOf(e);
        r > -1 && Hf.splice(r, 1)
    }
    ), [t]),
    {
        ...t,
        toast: oue,
        dismiss: r => Yc({
            type: ki.DISMISS_TOAST,
            toastId: r
        })
    }
}
